Package Presentation.Exceptions

  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    ClientException
    Super class for all client-related exceptions.
    DuplicateException
    Used when the same entry appears twice in database
    InvalidInputException
    Used in any command, when user-input does not meet requirements.
    NoMatchException
    Used when two input fields do not match.
    NoSuchCarportException
    Used in any command, when a carport with specified id, doesn't exist in database.
    NoSuchMaterialException
    Used in any command, when a material with specified id, doesn't exist in database.
    NoSuchPrebuiltCarportException
    Used in any command, when a prebuilt carport with specified id, doesn't exist in database.
    NoSuchRequestException
    Used in any command, when a request with specified id, doesn't exist in database.
    NoSuchResponseException
    Used in any command, when a response with specified id, doesn't exist in database.
    NoSuchRoofException
    Used in any command, when a roof with specified id, doesn't exist in database.
    NoSuchShedException
    Used in any command, when a shed with specified id, doesn't exist in database.
    SystemErrorException
    Super class of all exceptions related to system errors.
    UserNotFoundException
    Used in any command, when a user with specified id, doesn't exist in database.
